page.title: 11Wild Flowers on Blackcap
page.content: We went to Blackcap which is on the Downs outside Lewes.First we went on the eastern side of the path.This was an area grassland and scrub land.The flowers we saw most of here were the Common Spotted Orchid and the Common Rock Rose.Others we saw on this side of the path were: Early purple orchid,Smooth hawksbeard,Bacon and eggs,Common spotted orchid,Red clover,White spotted orchid,Common speedwell,Common rockrose,Fairy flax, Daisys,Common chickweed,Buttercup Forget_me_not and White clover. We went over to the western side of the path.It was bushy,prickily grassland. The flowers we saw on the this side were:Red Clover, Wild strawberry,Musk Thistle, Common Sorrol,Houry Crest,Dandilion,Yellow ruttle,Tufted vetch and Meddick.
